      "content": "but support is useless, they just give me these canned responses like nothing is wrong. it feels like they're covering for each other. i've been doing a lot of reading about how these massive platforms use automated systems to shadowban or even completely excise certain identities to keep their datasets \"clean\" or manageable. it's not even about a hack, it's about the system just deciding i shouldn't be there. don't you think it's possible they have protocols for this kind of digital erasure?",
